  "stem": "<p>In right triangle <math><mi>R</mi><mi>S</mi><mi>T</mi></math>, the sum of the measures of angle <math><mi>R</mi></math> and angle <math><mi>S</mi></math> is <math><mn>90</mn></math> degrees. The value of <math><mi>sin</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>R</mi><mo>)</mo></math> is <math><mfrac><msqrt><mn>7</mn></msqrt><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>. What is the value of <math><mi>cos</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>S</mi><mo>)</mo></math>?</p>",
  "answerOptions": [
    {
      "id": "a",
      "content": "<p><math><mfrac><msqrt><mn>7</mn></msqrt><mn>7</mn></mfrac></math></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "b",
      "content": "<p><math><mfrac><mn>3</mn><msqrt><mn>7</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "c",
      "content": "<p><math><mfrac><msqrt><mn>7</mn></msqrt><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "d",
      "content": "<p><math><msqrt><mn>7</mn></msqrt></math></p>"
    }
  ],
  "keys": [
    "c"
  ],
  "rationale": "<p>Choice C is correct. Since angles R and S are complementary (sum to 90\u00b0), cos(S) = sin(R) = \u221a7/3.</p><p>The other choices come from common reciprocal or simplification errors.</p>",
